For a coal power plant investment in Germany, they give 14 years of full allocations.
There is no price incentive at all to switch from coal to gas, which was the cheapest option available in Europe to cut down CO2 emissions.
The German and Polish allocation plans are scandalous.
They destroy the whole system of incentives.
