These were further developed in the Green Paper on a European strategy for sustainable, competitive and secure energy.
The Commission aims gradually to reduce the EUâs dependency on imported oil by creating energy efficiency, on the one hand, and by replacing it, on the other hand, with other energy sources, including biomass and other renewables.
It also aims at strengthening the producer-consumer dialogue with oil-producing countries in order to promote new exploration and development to meet rising global demand; promoting transparency and predictability of the oil market and being well prepared for emergencies, especially by ensuring that Member States maintain the stocks as set out in the relevant EU legislation.
It is important to know that all these policies â the ones on the use of fuel for cars, biomass and all the other measures just mentioned â will have a beneficial impact mainly in the medium to long term and not for the immediate future.
